-- #101 round: locks C round() (half AWAY from zero) on wasm against the double-rounding
-- bug in a naive `floor(abs(x)+0.5)`.  Regression for the $mdk_round fix.
--
-- Case B (the big one, ~2^52 inputs): an odd-integer double in [2^52, 2^53) is already
-- integral, so round must return it unchanged — but `x+0.5` is an EXACT tie that IEEE
-- half-to-even rounds UP, so the naive form returned x+1.  Here xB = 2^52+1; a correct
-- round gives `round xB - xB == 0.0`, the buggy one gives 1.0.
-- Case A: xA = 0.5 - 2^-54 = 0.49999999999999994; round -> 0.0 (naive -> 1.0, because
-- xA+0.5 rounds to exactly 1.0 before the floor).
--
-- Values are built with pow/intToFloat, NOT float literals: a literal >= 1e15 is itself
-- miscompiled by the native %.12g path (#57), and the off-by-1 is HIDDEN by
-- floatToString's 12-sig-fig truncation — so Case B is AMPLIFIED as `round xB - xB`.
-- eval == native == wasm.  Output: 0.0 0.0 3.0 -3.0
two = intToFloat 2
xB = pow two (intToFloat 52) + intToFloat 1
xA = intToFloat 1 / two - pow two (intToFloat 0 - intToFloat 54)
sep = " "
main = putStrLn (floatToString (round xB - xB) ++ sep ++ floatToString (round xA) ++ sep ++ floatToString (round 2.5) ++ sep ++ floatToString (round (intToFloat 0 - 2.5)))
